    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** as the clear anchor of the lineup; his 83.29 score is significantly boosted by a favorable matchup against Adrian Houser and an elite 16% park factor advantage, making him our primary engine for Runs and RBI. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (70.87) and **Marcell Ozuna** (67.72) follow as our top power threats, with the latter benefiting from a +10% wind-out factor that pushes his scoring ceiling despite a middling matchup against Jameson Taillon. While **Kyle Tucker** faces a daunting challenge against an elite arm in Jacob deGrom, his underlying talent keeps him above the start-threshold, though the -16% SP skill penalty serves as a stark reminder of the volatility involved in this matchup.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today was excluding **Nolan Schanuel** from the active lineup. Despite a respectable score of 56.62, he was edged out by the superior efficiency scores of our outfield depth, specifically **Heliot Ramos** (59.21) and **Jackson Merrill** (58.07), who both benefit from more favorable park environments. While **Nolan Schanuel** remains a high-floor asset, the optimizer prioritized the specific park-adjusted production of our other options. Managers should note that **Luis Robert Jr.** warrants close monitoring; his score dipped to 55.30 due to a severe -15% platoon penalty against Aaron Civale, marking him as a high-risk starter compared to the more insulated profiles of **Miguel Vargas** or **Drake Baldwin**.\n\nFinally, keep a close eye on the late-breaking lineup cards. Our entire strategy is predicated on the assumed positions, and any drop in the batting order for **Drake Baldwin** or **Miguel Vargas** would necessitate a recalculation of their respective order-based bonuses. We are leaning into our speed-focused outfielders today, with **Josh Lowe** active despite a difficult platoon split, specifically to leverage his potential for stolen bases\u2014our scarcest category. Be prepared to pivot if weather patterns shift, particularly at parks where wind-out bonuses are currently bolstering the scores of **Marcell Ozuna**, **Jackson Merrill**, and **Miguel Vargas**.",
